Business Brief -- Belvedere Corp.:
   Owner Makes Offer to Buy
   Rest of Shares for $6 Each
The majority owner is Christiania General Insurance Corp.,
the U.S. unit UNI Storebrand A/S of Norway.
   The offer, disclosed after the end of trading Friday, is
valued at about $16 million. In American Stock Exchange
trading, Belvedere closed at $4.375, unchanged.